<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The most in-depth study of the Patriot psychology is Edwin G. Burrows and Michael Wallace, "The American Revolution: The Ideology and Psychology of National Liberation," <i>Perspectives in American History,</i> (1972) vol. 6 pp 167-306</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://revolution.h-net.msu.edu/essays/irvin.feathers.html">Benjamin H. Irvin, "Tar and Feathers in Revolutionary America," (2003)</a></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Patriot_(American_Revolution)&action=edit&section=10.php.html" title="Edit section: Bibliography">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Bibliography">Bibliography</span></h2>
<ul>
